<section id="prepare" class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white border-t border-brand-line" aria-labelledby="prepare-heading">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-16">
      <div>
        <p class="text-brand-red font-bold text-xs tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">Before the visit</p>
        <h2 id="prepare-heading" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-black mb-4">
          How to Prepare
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-bold text-brand-red">1.</span>
            Prioritize your task list from most to least important.
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-bold text-brand-red">2.</span>
            Gather clear photographs of each item and note access limitations.
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-bold text-brand-red">3.</span>
            Have customer-supplied materials onsite and ready before the appointment.
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="font-bold text-brand-red">4.</span>
            Ensure we can access the work areas at the scheduled time.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-brand-red font-bold text-xs tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">Materials &amp; time</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-black mb-4">
          Materials and Additional Time
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Materials and specialty equipment are additional unless explicitly included. If something
          takes longer than expected, we will discuss options before performing additional time —
          nothing is added without your approval.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          If a task turns out to be unsafe, concealed, specialized, or more complex than expected, we
          may recommend a revised estimate or a return visit rather than forcing it into the reserved
          block.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
